To use a Mantine Modal and set its body content, you typically use the `Modal` component and place your content inside it. Here’s a basic example:

````tsx
// Example Mantine Modal body content
import { Modal, Button } from '@mantine/core';
import { useState } from 'react';

function DemoModal() {
  const [opened, setOpened] = useState(false);

  return (
    <>
      <Button onClick={() => setOpened(true)}>Open Modal</Button>
      <Modal opened={opened} onClose={() => setOpened(false)} title="Modal Title">
        {/* Modal body content goes here */}
        <div>
          This is the body of the Mantine Modal.
        </div>
      </Modal>
    </>
  );
}
````

Place any JSX inside the `<Modal>` to define its body.

